parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels excessively
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle drags
a burning odor is present
the brake light illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake locks up on the road
the tire blows out before the vehicle can be stopped
the parking brake must be disconnected on the side of the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: Boiling brake fluid
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the autobrake system can cause the vehicle to become immobilized, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, which can be extremely dangerous to occupants and other traffic.
symptoms: The autobrake system fails to engage or disengage properly
causing the vehicle to become stuck or move unexpectedly
resulting in loss of control
sudden slowing down
or violent deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or damage to property, which can be dangerous to occupants and other traffic.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage or hold
causing the vehicle to roll or move
requiring the use of external means to prevent movement
such as placing objects behind the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the parking brake while driving can cause the vehicle to suddenly slow down or lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can be dangerous to occupants and other traffic.
symptoms: The parking brake engages unexpectedly while driving
causing the vehicle to slow down or decelerate rapidly
producing unusual smells or sounds
such as burning rubber.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of brake and steering power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the ignition switch melts
the vehicle loses brake and steering power
the dashboard and starter have no power
the vehicle is unable to start.
